r engagement? How do I make money from my podcast? These are questions that most podcast hosts will have asked themselves at some point in their journey. When used to their full potential, "),(0,a.n)(a.j,{className:(0,a.u)("plasmic_default__all","plasmic_default__a","__wab_text","plasmic_default__inline","_9PodcasterGuide__link__wUjj9"),component:_.default,href:"https://fountain.fm/faqs/value-for-value",platform:"nextjs",target:"_blank"},"Value for Value"),(0,a.n)(l.Fragment,null,` podcast apps like Fountain are the answer. Before we get into the seven steps that will help to you get the most out of Fountain, let's look at each of these questions in turn.

`),(0,a.n)("span",{className:"plasmic_default__all plasmic_default__span",style:{fontWeight:700,color:"#000000"}},"How do I make money from my podcast?"),(0,a.n)(l.Fragment,null,`

Most podcasts are available to listeners for free on any podcast app - which is how it should be if they are going to reach the widest potential audience. But how do podcasters monetise their content? If you have already built a large audience, you might have sponsors or ads. You might also try offering exclusive content, ad-free feeds or early access to members behind a paywall. Or you might decide to be 100% audience-funded through donations. Whatever the business model is for your podcast, Value for Value is complementary. 

On Fountain, your fans can show their support as they are listening by sending small units of bitcoin called sats over the `),(0,a.n)(a.j,{className:(0,a.u)("plasmic_default__all","plasmic_default__a","__wab_text","plasmic_default__inline","_9PodcasterGuide__link__aZqOj"),component:_.default,href:"https://support.fountain.fm/article/22-what-is-the-bitcoin-lightning-network",platform:"nextjs",target:"_blank"},"Lightning Network"),(0,a.n)(l.Fragment,null,`. The value of bitcoin changes daily, but $1 is equivalent to roughly 4000 sats. If they receive a lot of value from a particular episode, they can pay more. If they weren't feeling it, they can pay less - or nothing at all. All listeners need to do is download the Fountain app, top up their wallet with a bank card and start supporting.

`),(0,a.n)("span",{className:"plasmic_default__all plasmic_default__span",style:{fontWeight:700,color:"#000000"}},"How do I get more listeners?"),(0,a.n)(l.Fragment,null,`

Value for Value is more than just a new revenue stream for your podcast. After all, making money may be less important than getting your content out there and reaching new listeners. As a creator, your primary purpose is to create content that your audience finds valuable. "Build it and they will come", as the saying goes. But it's not always that simple. Although you might not have the time, energy or skillset required to do effective marketing for your podcast, your most passionate fans will.

On Fountain, your listeners are your marketing department. Every time they send a boost or create a clip, this activity is seen in the Fountain Discover feed. This is a powerful signal can grab the attention of listeners who may not have seen or heard your podcast before. Asking your listeners to support you on Fountain not only helps your podcast make money, but it helps your podcast grow.

`),(0,a.n)("span",{className:"plasmic_default__all plasmic_default__span",style:{fontWeight:700,color:"#000000"}},"How do I generate better engagement?"),(0,a.n)(l.Fragment,null,`

Value for Value allows you to build relationships with your listeners and interact with them in ways that are simply not possible through most podcast apps. Fountain offers your listeners a place where they can meet and interact with each other or reach out to you, your co-hosts and guests directly. Getting positive feedback from your listeners is also incredibly important for keeping you motivated and inspired for years to come. 90% of podcasts don\u2019t survive past episode 3, but with the support of your listeners, all that hard work you put into your podcast feels worthwhile.`))),((0,a.m)(e,"screen","mobileOnly"),(0,a.n)("div",{"data-plasmic-override":t.introduction3,className:(0,a.u)("plasmic_default__all","plasmic_default__div","_9PodcasterGuide__introduction3__h6JUz")},(0,a.m)(e,"screen","mobileOnly")?(0,a.n)("h3",{className:(0,a.u)("plasmic_default__all","plasmic_default__h3","__wab_text","_9PodcasterGuide__h3__ukYzM")},(0,a.m)(e,"screen","mobileOnly")?"How it works":"Top claimed shows"):null,(0,a.n)("h6",{className:(0,a.u)("plasmic_default__all","plasmic_default__h6","__wab_text","_9PodcasterGuide__h6__qsaH")},"The Value for Value model has the potential to transform discovery, engagement and monetisation for your podcast, but it might not be obvious where or how to get started. Here are seven steps you should follow to build a strong community of supporters on Fountain."),(0,a.m)(e,"screen","mobileOnly")?(0,a.n)("div",{className:(0,a.u)("plasmic_default__all","plasmic_default__div","_9PodcasterGuide__freeBox__nSaIq")},((0,a.m)(e,"screen","mobileOnly"),(0,a.n)("div",{className:(0,a.u)("plasmic_default__all","plasmic_default__div","_9PodcasterGuide__freeBox__sWfDm")},(0,a.n)(a.i,{alt:"",className:(0,a.u)("_9PodcasterGuide__img__kv2Gj"),displayHeight:"auto",displayMaxHeight:"none",displayMaxWidth:"100%",displayMinHeight:"0",displayMinWidth:"0",displayWidth:"auto",loader:"plasmic",loading:"lazy",src:{src:"https://img.plasmic.app/img-optimizer/v1/img/fec97aaa9